The categorization of the body scanner market by product type highlights the varied applications of these devices in different settings. Full-body scanners are gaining popularity in high-security facilities, airports, and seaports for comprehensive security checks, while metal detectors are commonly used in public spaces to identify metal objects on individuals. Explosive trace detectors (ETD) serve a crucial role in detecting explosive materials, providing an additional layer of security in sensitive areas such as border checkpoints and critical infrastructure facilities. The versatility of body scanners in different product types demonstrates their adaptability to diverse security requirements.

In terms of applications, the body scanner market is witnessing significant demand from the transport sector, particularly airports, where ensuring passenger safety is paramount. The critical infrastructure protection segment is also driving market growth, with body scanners being deployed in key facilities like power plants and government buildings to prevent unauthorized access. Furthermore, border security remains a crucial application area for body scanners, aiding in the screening of individuals and goods entering a country to counter illicit activities.

